Note: HIR to Elixir Translator for Translation Translation System
Note: Converts High-level Intermediate Representation to idiomatic Elixir code


@Reasoning:
Translator state for the legacy String-concatenation Elixir backend.
Tracks output buffer, indent depth, and contextual fields (current
module, current function, pattern-match scope, actor-model scope, OTP
behaviour) that downstream emitters need to produce idiomatic Elixir.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Eight fields covering output, indent, current_module/function name
context, pattern and actor-model dicts, OTP behaviour name, and
requires_newline flag for line-break decisions between statements.
@End Implementation

Type called "HIRToElixirTranslator":
    output_buffer as String
    indentation_level as Integer
    current_module as String
    current_function as String
    pattern_context as Integer
    actor_model_context as Integer
    otp_behavior_context as String
    requires_newline as Integer
End Type

@Reasoning:
Construct a fresh translator with empty buffers and zeroed context.
Called once per HIR -> Elixir translation.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Builds an HIRToElixirTranslator with output_buffer "", indent 0, empty
current_module/function, fresh pattern_context and actor_model_context
dicts, empty otp_behavior_context, requires_newline 0.
@End Implementation

Process called "create_hir_to_elixir_translator" returns Integer:
    Note: Create new HIR to Elixir translator instance

    Let translator be a value of type HIRToElixirTranslator with
        output_buffer as "",
        indentation_level as 0,
        current_module as "",
        current_function as "",
        pattern_context as proc create_dict,
        actor_model_context as proc create_dict,
        otp_behavior_context as "",
        requires_newline as 0

    Return translator
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: DISPATCHER ENTRY POINT
Note: ============================================================================
Note: Single-arg wrapper matching the central dispatcher call shape in
Note: translation.runa: `Return proc hir_to_elixir from ElixirEmitter with hir_root`.
Note: Constructs a fresh HIRToElixirTranslator and routes through
Note: translate_hir_to_elixir which holds the actual translation pipeline.
Note: Introduced in P2-F Round 2B alongside the demolition of the vestigial
Note: elixir_emitter.runa shim.
@Reasoning:
Single-argument dispatcher entry point matching the call shape used in
the central translation router. Constructs a translator and delegates
to translate_hir_to_elixir.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null root returns 0. Otherwise creates a translator (returns 0 on
allocation failure), runs translate_hir_to_elixir, returns the
accumulated output string.
@End Implementation

Process called "hir_to_elixir" takes hir_root as Integer returns Integer:
    If hir_root is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let translator be proc create_hir_to_elixir_translator
    If translator is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let elixir_code be proc translate_hir_to_elixir with translator, hir_root
    Return elixir_code
End Process

@Reasoning:
Main HIR node dispatcher. Routes based on Elixir-specific node_type
strings ("module", "function", "actor_receive", "actor_spawn",
"otp_genserver_call", etc.) to specialised translators. Elixir's actor
model and OTP behaviours need explicit handling because they map to
specific module/function patterns rather than generic constructs.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads node_type via dict lookup. Match statement dispatches across the
21 known kinds. Unknown nodes emit "# Unknown HIR node: ..." as an
Elixir comment so callers can spot translation gaps. Returns
translator.output_buffer.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_hir_to_elixir" takes translator as Integer, hir as Integer returns String:
    Note: Translate HIR to idiomatic Elixir code with actor model and OTP support

    Let node_type be proc get_dict_value with hir, "node_type"

    Match node_type:
        When "module":
            proc translate_module with translator, hir
        When "function":
            proc translate_function with translator, hir
        When "pattern_match":
            proc translate_pattern_match with translator, hir
        When "match_clause":
            proc translate_match_clause with translator, hir
        When "actor_receive":
            proc translate_receive with translator, hir
        When "actor_spawn":
            proc translate_spawn with translator, hir
        When "actor_send":
            proc translate_send with translator, hir
        When "otp_genserver_call":
            proc translate_genserver_call with translator, hir
        When "otp_genserver_cast":
            proc translate_genserver_cast with translator, hir
        When "function_composition":
            proc translate_pipe with translator, hir
        When "list_comprehension":
            proc translate_for_comprehension with translator, hir
        When "tuple":
            proc translate_tuple with translator, hir
        When "map":
            proc translate_map with translator, hir
        When "list":
            proc translate_list with translator, hir
        When "atom":
            proc translate_atom with translator, hir
        When "string_literal":
            proc translate_string with translator, hir
        When "number_literal":
            proc translate_number with translator, hir
        When "binary_operation":
            proc translate_binary_operation with translator, hir
        When "function_call":
            proc translate_function_call with translator, hir
        When "variable":
            proc translate_variable with translator, hir
        When "assignment":
            proc translate_assignment with translator, hir
        When "conditional":
            proc translate_conditional with translator, hir
        Otherwise:
            proc emit with translator, "# Unknown HIR node: "
            proc emit with translator, node_type
    End Match

    Return translator.output_buffer
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit "defmodule Name do ... end". The Elixir module is the primary
unit of namespacing and code organisation.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads name, sets current_module on the translator (for nested
emitters to reference). Emits "defmodule Name do", indents, walks
declarations, dedents, emits "end".
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_module" takes translator as Integer, hir as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate HIR module to Elixir module

    Let module_name be proc get_dict_value with hir, "name"
    Set translator.current_module to module_name

    proc emit_line with translator, "defmodule "
    proc emit with translator, module_name
    proc emit_line with translator, " do"
    proc indent from translator

    Note: Handle OTP behavior
    Let otp_behavior be proc get_dict_value with hir, "otp_behavior"
    If otp_behavior is not equal to 0:
        Set translator.otp_behavior_context to otp_behavior
        proc emit_line with translator, "use "
        proc emit with translator, otp_behavior
        proc emit_newline from translator
    End If

    Note: Handle module attributes
    Let attributes be proc get_dict_value with hir, "attributes"
    If attributes is not equal to 0:
        proc translate_module_attributes with translator, attributes
    End If

    Note: Translate module body
    Let body be proc get_dict_value with hir, "body"
    If body is not equal to 0:
        proc translate_statement_list with translator, body
    End If

    proc dedent from translator
    proc emit_line with translator, "end"

    Set translator.current_module to ""
    Set translator.otp_behavior_context to ""

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit "def name(args) do body end" for a regular function, or
"defp name(args) do body end" for a private one. Private functions
are signalled by a flag in the HIR.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads name, parameter list, body, and is_private flag. Emits "def "
(or "defp "), the name, "(" + parameters + ")", " do" + LF, body at
+1 indent, then "end".
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_function" takes translator as Integer, hir as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate HIR function to Elixir def

    Let function_name be proc get_dict_value with hir, "name"
    Set translator.current_function to function_name

    Note: Check if this is an OTP callback
    Let otp_callback be proc get_dict_value with hir, "otp_callback"
    If otp_callback is not equal to 0:
        proc emit_line with translator, "@impl true"
    End If

    Note: Handle function visibility
    Let visibility be proc get_dict_value with hir, "visibility"
    If visibility is equal to "private":
        proc emit with translator, "defp "
    Otherwise:
        proc emit with translator, "def "
    End If

    proc emit with translator, function_name

    Note: Handle function clauses (pattern matching)
    Let clauses be proc get_dict_value with hir, "clauses"
    If clauses is not equal to 0:
        proc translate_function_clauses with translator, clauses
    Otherwise:
        Note: Single function definition
        Let parameters be proc get_dict_value with hir, "parameters"
        If parameters is not equal to 0:
            proc emit with translator, "("
            proc translate_parameters with translator, parameters
            proc emit with translator, ")"
        End If

        Note: Handle guards
        Let guards be proc get_dict_value with hir, "guards"
        If guards is not equal to 0:
            proc emit with translator, " when "
            proc translate_guards with translator, guards
        End If

        proc emit with translator, " do"
        proc emit_newline from translator
        proc indent from translator

        Let body be proc get_dict_value with hir, "body"
        If body is not equal to 0:
            proc translate_statement_list with translator, body
        End If

        proc dedent from translator
        proc emit_line with translator, "end"
    End If

    Set translator.current_function to ""

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit a "case expr do ... end" block for HIR pattern_match nodes.
Multi-arm patterns are emitted as case clauses.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits "case " + expression + " do" + LF. Walks clauses calling
translate_match_clause for each. Closes with "end".
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_pattern_match" takes translator as Integer, hir as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate HIR pattern match to Elixir case

    proc emit with translator, "case "
    Let expression be proc get_dict_value with hir, "expression"
    proc translate_hir_to_elixir with translator, expression
    proc emit_line with translator, " do"

    proc indent from translator

    Let clauses be proc get_dict_value with hir, "clauses"
    If clauses is not equal to 0:
        Let clause_count be proc get_list_size from clauses
        Let index be 0

        While index is less than clause_count:
            Let clause be proc get_list_item with clauses, index
            proc translate_match_clause with translator, clause
            Set index to index plus 1
        End While
    End If

    proc dedent from translator
    proc emit_line with translator, "end"

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit a single case/receive match clause "pattern -> body".
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits indented pattern via translate_pattern, " -> ", then body
expression. Optional "when" guard between pattern and "->" when
present.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_match_clause" takes translator as Integer, clause as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate single match clause

    Let pattern be proc get_dict_value with clause, "pattern"
    Let guard be proc get_dict_value with clause, "guard"
    Let body be proc get_dict_value with clause, "body"

    proc emit_indent from translator
    proc translate_pattern with translator, pattern

    If guard is not equal to 0:
        proc emit with translator, " when "
        proc translate_hir_to_elixir with translator, guard
    End If

    proc emit_line with translator, " ->"
    proc indent from translator

    proc translate_hir_to_elixir with translator, body

    proc dedent from translator
    proc emit_newline from translator

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Translate an HIR pattern to Elixir pattern syntax. Patterns include
wildcards (_), variables, literals, tuples ({a, b}), maps (%{...}),
lists ([head | tail]), and binary structures.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads pattern's kind. Wildcard emits "_". Variable emits name.
Literal recurses through the literal emitters. Tuple emits
"{p1, p2, ...}". Map emits "%{k => v, ...}". List emits "[p1, p2,
... | rest]" with optional rest.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_pattern" takes translator as Integer, pattern as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate HIR pattern to Elixir pattern

    Let pattern_type be proc get_dict_value with pattern, "node_type"

    Match pattern_type:
        When "variable":
            Let var_name be proc get_dict_value with pattern, "name"
            proc emit with translator, var_name

        When "tuple_pattern":
            proc emit with translator, "{"
            Let elements be proc get_dict_value with pattern, "elements"
            proc translate_pattern_list with translator, elements, ", "
            proc emit with translator, "}"

        When "list_pattern":
            proc translate_list_pattern with translator, pattern

        When "map_pattern":
            proc translate_map_pattern with translator, pattern

        When "atom":
            proc emit with translator, ":"
            Let value be proc get_dict_value with pattern, "value"
            proc emit with translator, value

        When "string_literal":
            proc emit with translator, "\""
            Set value to proc get_dict_value with pattern, "value"
            proc emit with translator, proc escape_elixir_string from value
            proc emit with translator, "\""

        When "number_literal":
            Set value to proc get_dict_value with pattern, "value"
            proc emit with translator, value

        Otherwise:
            proc translate_hir_to_elixir with translator, pattern
    End Match

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit Elixir actor-receive: "receive do clauses end" with optional
"after timeout -> body" tail. Used in actor processes to wait for
messages.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits "receive do" + LF. Walks the receive clauses calling
translate_match_clause for each pattern -> body pair. If a timeout
arm exists, emits "after timeout -> body". Closes with "end".
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_receive" takes translator as Integer, hir as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate HIR actor receive to Elixir receive

    proc emit_line with translator, "receive do"
    proc indent from translator

    Let clauses be proc get_dict_value with hir, "clauses"
    If clauses is not equal to 0:
        Let clause_count be proc get_list_size from clauses
        Let index be 0

        While index is less than clause_count:
            Let clause be proc get_list_item with clauses, index
            proc translate_receive_clause with translator, clause
            Set index to index plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Note: Handle after clause (timeout)
    Let after_clause be proc get_dict_value with hir, "after"
    If after_clause is not equal to 0:
        Let timeout be proc get_dict_value with after_clause, "timeout"
        Let timeout_body be proc get_dict_value with after_clause, "body"

        proc emit_indent from translator
        proc translate_hir_to_elixir with translator, timeout
        proc emit_line with translator, " ->"
        proc indent from translator
        proc translate_hir_to_elixir with translator, timeout_body
        proc dedent from translator
    End If

    proc dedent from translator
    proc emit_line with translator, "end"

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit "spawn(fn -> body end)" or "spawn_link" depending on link flag.
Spawns a new actor process running the provided body expression.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads link flag and body expression. Emits "spawn" or "spawn_link",
then "(fn -> ", body, " end)".
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_spawn" takes translator as Integer, hir as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate HIR actor spawn to Elixir spawn

    Let spawn_type be proc get_dict_value with hir, "spawn_type"

    Match spawn_type:
        When "spawn":
            proc emit with translator, "spawn("
        When "spawn_link":
            proc emit with translator, "spawn_link("
        When "spawn_monitor":
            proc emit with translator, "spawn_monitor("
        When "Task.start":
            proc emit with translator, "Task.start("
        Otherwise:
            proc emit with translator, "spawn("
    End Match

    Let module_name be proc get_dict_value with hir, "module"
    Let function_name be proc get_dict_value with hir, "function"
    Let arguments be proc get_dict_value with hir, "arguments"

    If module_name is not equal to 0:
        proc emit with translator, module_name
        proc emit with translator, ", :"
        proc emit with translator, function_name
    Otherwise:
        proc emit with translator, "fn -> "
        proc emit with translator, function_name
    End If

    If arguments is not equal to 0:
        proc emit with translator, ", ["
        proc translate_argument_list with translator, arguments
        proc emit with translator, "]"
    Otherwise:
        proc emit with translator, ", []"
    End If

    If module_name is equal to 0:
        proc emit with translator, " end"
    End If

    proc emit with translator, ")"

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit "send(pid, message)". Sends a message asynchronously to an
actor process; no reply is awaited.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads target_pid and message expressions. Emits "send(", recursively
translates each, separates with ", ", emits ")".
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_send" takes translator as Integer, hir as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate HIR actor send to Elixir send

    proc emit with translator, "send("

    Let target be proc get_dict_value with hir, "target"
    Let message be proc get_dict_value with hir, "message"

    proc translate_hir_to_elixir with translator, target
    proc emit with translator, ", "
    proc translate_hir_to_elixir with translator, message

    proc emit with translator, ")"

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit "GenServer.call(server, message)". Synchronous OTP request-reply
to a GenServer; the caller blocks until the server responds.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads server reference and message expressions. Emits
"GenServer.call(", translates server, ", ", message, ")".
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_genserver_call" takes translator as Integer, hir as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate HIR GenServer call to Elixir GenServer.call

    proc emit with translator, "GenServer.call("

    Let server be proc get_dict_value with hir, "server"
    Let request be proc get_dict_value with hir, "request"
    Let timeout be proc get_dict_value with hir, "timeout"

    proc translate_hir_to_elixir with translator, server
    proc emit with translator, ", "
    proc translate_hir_to_elixir with translator, request

    If timeout is not equal to 0:
        proc emit with translator, ", "
        proc translate_hir_to_elixir with translator, timeout
    End If

    proc emit with translator, ")"

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit "GenServer.cast(server, message)". Asynchronous fire-and-forget
request to a GenServer; the caller does not wait for a reply.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits "GenServer.cast(" + server + ", " + message + ")" by recursing
into the operand expressions.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_genserver_cast" takes translator as Integer, hir as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate HIR GenServer cast to Elixir GenServer.cast

    proc emit with translator, "GenServer.cast("

    Let server be proc get_dict_value with hir, "server"
    Let request be proc get_dict_value with hir, "request"

    proc translate_hir_to_elixir with translator, server
    proc emit with translator, ", "
    proc translate_hir_to_elixir with translator, request

    proc emit with translator, ")"

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit Elixir pipeline operator chain "a |> f |> g". The HIR
function_composition node carries a list of stages to be chained.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits the first stage, then for each subsequent stage emits " |> "
followed by the stage expression. Stages are translated via the main
dispatcher.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_pipe" takes translator as Integer, hir as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate HIR function composition to Elixir pipe

    Let input be proc get_dict_value with hir, "input"
    Let transform be proc get_dict_value with hir, "transform"

    proc translate_hir_to_elixir with translator, input
    proc emit with translator, " |> "
    proc translate_hir_to_elixir with translator, transform

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit Elixir "for" list comprehension "for x <- xs, filter, do:
expr". Supports generators, filters, and a body expression.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits "for ", then comma-separated generators ("var <- source") and
filters (boolean expressions). Then emits ", do: " followed by the
body expression.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_for_comprehension" takes translator as Integer, hir as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate HIR list comprehension to Elixir for

    proc emit with translator, "for "

    Let generators be proc get_dict_value with hir, "generators"
    If generators is not equal to 0:
        proc translate_generators with translator, generators
    End If

    Let filters be proc get_dict_value with hir, "filters"
    If filters is not equal to 0:
        proc emit with translator, ", "
        proc translate_filters with translator, filters
    End If

    Let into_clause be proc get_dict_value with hir, "into"
    If into_clause is not equal to 0:
        proc emit with translator, ", into: "
        proc translate_hir_to_elixir with translator, into_clause
    End If

    proc emit with translator, ", do: "

    Let transform be proc get_dict_value with hir, "transform"
    proc translate_hir_to_elixir with translator, transform

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit Elixir tuple "{a, b, c}". Tuples are first-class fixed-size
ordered values; commonly used for tagged unions ({:ok, value} or
{:error, reason}).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits "{", iterates elements with ", " separators recursing into the
dispatcher, emits "}".
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_tuple" takes translator as Integer, hir as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate HIR tuple to Elixir tuple

    proc emit with translator, "{"

    Let elements be proc get_dict_value with hir, "elements"
    If elements is not equal to 0:
        proc translate_expression_list with translator, elements, ", "
    End If

    proc emit with translator, "}"

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit Elixir map "%{key => value, ...}". When keys are atoms can also
use the short form %{key: value}; this emitter always uses the
explicit "=>" form.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits "%{", iterates the entries emitting "key => value" pairs with
", " separators, emits "}".
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_map" takes translator as Integer, hir as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate HIR map to Elixir map

    proc emit with translator, "%{"

    Let pairs be proc get_dict_value with hir, "pairs"
    If pairs is not equal to 0:
        Let pair_count be proc get_list_size from pairs
        Let index be 0

        While index is less than pair_count:
            If index is greater than 0:
                proc emit with translator, ", "
            End If

            Let pair be proc get_list_item with pairs, index
            Let key be proc get_dict_value with pair, "key"
            Let value be proc get_dict_value with pair, "value"

            proc translate_hir_to_elixir with translator, key
            proc emit with translator, " => "
            proc translate_hir_to_elixir with translator, value

            Set index to index plus 1
        End While
    End If

    proc emit with translator, "}"

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit Elixir list "[a, b, c]". Elixir lists are linked-list cons cells;
the literal syntax is the same as most languages.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits "[", iterates elements with ", " separators, emits "]".
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_list" takes translator as Integer, hir as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate HIR list to Elixir list

    proc emit with translator, "["

    Let elements be proc get_dict_value with hir, "elements"
    If elements is not equal to 0:
        proc translate_expression_list with translator, elements, ", "
    End If

    proc emit with translator, "]"

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit an Elixir atom literal ":name". Atoms are interned symbolic
constants used for tags, status codes, and module references.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the atom name, emits ":" + name.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_atom" takes translator as Integer, hir as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate HIR atom to Elixir atom

    proc emit with translator, ":"
    Let value be proc get_dict_value with hir, "value"
    proc emit with translator, value

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit a double-quoted Elixir string literal. Elixir strings are UTF-8
binaries; special characters must be escaped.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the literal value, runs it through escape_elixir_string to
handle quotes/backslashes/newlines, then emits '"' + escaped + '"'.
@End Implementation

@Security_Scope:
Strings are escaped before emission, so user-supplied content cannot
break out of the literal. Trusts the underlying escape function.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "translate_string" takes translator as Integer, hir as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate HIR string to Elixir string

    proc emit with translator, "\""
    Let value be proc get_dict_value with hir, "value"
    Let escaped_value be proc escape_elixir_string from value
    proc emit with translator, escaped_value
    proc emit with translator, "\""

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit an Elixir number literal. Elixir's numeric literal syntax (plain
decimal) matches Runa's, so the value is emitted verbatim.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the value and emits it as a string.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_number" takes translator as Integer, hir as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate HIR number to Elixir number

    Let value be proc get_dict_value with hir, "value"
    proc emit with translator, value

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit an Elixir variable reference. Variable names are emitted as-is;
Elixir uses snake_case by convention so the HIR name should already be
in the right shape.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the variable name from the HIR node and emits it.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_variable" takes translator as Integer, hir as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate HIR variable to Elixir variable

    Let name be proc get_dict_value with hir, "name"
    proc emit with translator, name

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit an Elixir function call "Module.function(args)" or "function
(args)". Module-qualified calls require a separate Module prefix.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads optional module name, function name, and argument list. Emits
"Module." prefix if present, then the function name, then "(",
arguments via translate_argument_list, ")".
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_function_call" takes translator as Integer, hir as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate HIR function call to Elixir function call

    Let function_name be proc get_dict_value with hir, "function"
    Let module_name be proc get_dict_value with hir, "module"
    Let arguments be proc get_dict_value with hir, "arguments"

    If module_name is not equal to 0:
        proc emit with translator, module_name
        proc emit with translator, "."
    End If

    proc emit with translator, function_name

    If arguments is not equal to 0:
        proc emit with translator, "("
        proc translate_argument_list with translator, arguments
        proc emit with translator, ")"
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

Note: Helper processes for HIR to Elixir translation

@Reasoning:
Walk a list of statements emitting each one on its own line. Used
inside function bodies, case clauses, and do/end blocks.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Iterates the statement list, dispatches each via the main
translate_hir_to_elixir router, emits a newline after each statement.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_statement_list" takes translator as Integer, statements as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate list of HIR statements to Elixir statements

    Let stmt_count be proc get_list_size from statements
    Let index be 0

    While index is less than stmt_count:
        Let statement be proc get_list_item with statements, index

        proc emit_indent from translator
        proc translate_hir_to_elixir with translator, statement
        proc emit_newline from translator

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit a comma-separated argument list for function calls.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Iterates the args list, recurses each via the main dispatcher, emits
", " between arguments but not after the last.
@End Implementation

Process called "translate_argument_list" takes translator as Integer, args as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate HIR arguments to Elixir argument list

    Let arg_count be proc get_list_size from args
    Let index be 0

    While index is less than arg_count:
        If index is greater than 0:
            proc emit with translator, ", "
        End If

        Let argument be proc get_list_item with args, index
        proc translate_hir_to_elixir with translator, argument

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Append text to the translator's output buffer. Lowest-level emission
primitive used by all other emit_* helpers.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Concatenates text onto translator.output_buffer.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
String-concat-based emission is O(n^2) in total output length. Fine
for typical Elixir module sizes, not for large outputs.
@End Performance_Hints

Process called "emit" takes translator as Integer, text as String returns Integer:
    Note: Emit text to output buffer
    Set translator.output_buffer to proc string_concat with translator.output_buffer, text
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit text followed by a newline plus the current indent prefix.
Pairs cleanly with emit-then-emit_line patterns inside translator
helpers.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits the text, then a LF, then indent_level * 2 spaces.
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_line" takes translator as Integer, text as String returns Integer:
    Note: Emit line with proper indentation
    proc emit_indent from translator
    proc emit with translator, text
    proc emit_newline from translator
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit a bare newline plus the current indent prefix.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Concatenates LF then indent_level * 2 spaces onto output_buffer.
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_newline" takes translator as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit newline character
    proc emit with translator, "\n"
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit the current indent prefix as standalone whitespace. Used when
splicing into a line that did not come through emit_line.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Loops indent_level times appending two spaces per level (Elixir
convention).
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_indent" takes translator as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit proper indentation

    Let spaces_per_level be 2
    Let total_spaces be translator.indentation_level multiplied by spaces_per_level
    Let space_count be 0

    While space_count is less than total_spaces:
        proc emit with translator, " "
        Set space_count to space_count plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Step into a deeper nesting level.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increments translator.indentation_level by 1.
@End Implementation

Process called "indent" takes translator as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Increase indentation level
    Set translator.indentation_level to translator.indentation_level plus 1
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Step out of a nested block. Clamped at zero so unmatched
indent/dedent calls do not underflow.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
If indentation_level > 0, decrements by 1.
@End Implementation

Process called "dedent" takes translator as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Decrease indentation level
    If translator.indentation_level is greater than 0:
        Set translator.indentation_level to translator.indentation_level minus 1
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Escape characters that would break a double-quoted Elixir string
literal: backslash, double-quote, and common control characters
(newline, tab, carriage return).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Walks each character of the input. Replaces backslash with "\\\\",
double-quote with "\\\"", newline with "\\n", carriage-return with
"\\r", tab with "\\t". Other characters pass through unchanged.
@End Implementation

@Security_Scope:
Prevents Elixir string-literal injection. Caller must invoke this
for any value embedded in a string literal.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "escape_elixir_string" takes text as String returns String:
    Note: Escape special characters in Elixir string

    Let result be ""
    Let length be length of text
    Let index be 0

    While index is less than length:
        Let char be proc char_at with text, index

        Match char:
            When "\"":
                Set result to proc string_concat with result, "\\\""
            When "\\":
                Set result to proc string_concat with result, "\\\\"
            When "\n":
                Set result to proc string_concat with result, "\\n"
            When "\t":
                Set result to proc string_concat with result, "\\t"
            When "\r":
                Set result to proc string_concat with result, "\\r"
            Otherwise:
                Set result to proc string_concat with result, char
        End Match

        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning:
Local helper to construct an empty dictionary for pattern and
actor-model context tracking inside the translator.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocates a new dict via the dictionary primitive (or returns a
shared empty-dict sentinel). Caller is expected to mutate via the
standard dict API.
@End Implementation

Process called "create_dict" returns Integer:
    Note: Create dictionary for storage
    Return proc memory_allocate from Layout with 24
End Process